DTSTAMP:20260513T104142Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a screening of documentary films by People's Archive of Rural India (PARI) that bring into focus the intertwined realities of climate change\, gender\, and labour across rural India. Through intimate and powerful storytelling\, these films trace how shifting ecologies reshape livelihoods\, deepen existing inequalities\, and place disproportionate burdens on women and marginalised communities. \n\nFrom farms and forests to coastlines and homes\, the screenings reveal stories of resilience\, adaptation\, and collective action in the face of environmental change. This programme invites audiences to reflect on climate justice not as an abstract future concern\, but as a lived present shaped by work\, care\, and survival.\n\n\n\nThis event is part of programming around Beneath the Turning Sky in collaboration with People’s Archives of Rural India (PARI)\n\n\n\n
